@{"   2.Summation Group     " link GR_me_subgrp_3}
@{"   3.Entry Fields        " link GR_me_subgrp_5}
@{"   4.Action Knobs        " link GR_me_subgrp_6}

@{" D.Preferences           " link WI_prefs}
@{"   1.First Page          " link GR_prefs_general}
@{"   2.Second Page         " link GR_sparte_col}

@{" E.Pull Down Menus       " link menu}
@ENDNODE

@NODE WI_hcm_main "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / A. Main Window"

@{b}A.Main Window@{ub}

 +------------------------------------------------------+
 | @{"        Toolbar        " link GR_tb_main}                              |
 |                                                      |
 |  |@{"Years" link GR_reg_years}|            |@{"Months" link GR_reg_months}|                        |
 |  |@{bg shine}      @{bg background}+------------|------|------------+           |
 |  |@{bg shine}@{fg fill}Year  All Costs  Fixcosts  Status@{fg text}      @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}1997    2231.23   1123.12  n/a         @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}|           |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}| @{bg fill}   Add   @{bg background} |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}| @{bg fill} Remove  @{bg background} |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}| @{bg fill}Fix costs@{bg background} |
 |  +---------------------------------------+           |
 | @{"                    Statusbar                       " link GR_main_bottom} |
 +------------------------------------------------------+

The main Money97 window is the center of operation. At the upper region of the window you find a @{"toolbar" link GR_tb_main} which lets you call the main functions of the program faster than using the menu. Nevertheless all toolbar functions are also accessible through the @{"pull down menus" link menu}.

The bottom part of the window ist covered by a @{"status bar" link GR_main_bottom} which displays the name of the project (i.e. the filename), the number of cost entries (@{"month entries" link "WI_month_edit"} plus all entries generated by the @{"fixcost editor" link "WI_fixcost_definer"}) and the sum over all years.

The biggest part of the window is covered by the Years/Months register. Have a look at the description of the @{"Years" link GR_reg_years}- and @{"Months" link GR_reg_months}-pages for further details.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_reg_years  "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / A.1 Years Page"

@{b}A.1 Years Register Page@{ub} - (Part of main window)

 +------------------------------------------------------+
 | @{"        Toolbar        " link GR_tb_main}                              |
 |                                                      |
 |  |@{bg shine}@{fg fill}Years@{fg text}@{bg background}|             |@{"Months" link GR_reg_months}|                        |
 |  |@{bg shine}      @{bg background}+------------|------|------------+           |
 |  |@{bg shine}@{fg fill}Year  All Costs  Fixcosts  Status@{fg text}      @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}1997    2231.23   1123.12  n/a         @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}|           |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}| @{bg fill}@{fg shine}   Add   @{fg text}@{bg background} |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}| @{bg fill}@{fg shine} Remove  @{fg text}@{bg background} |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                       @{bg background}| @{"Fix costs" link WI_fixcost_definer} |
 |  +---------------------------------------+           |
 | @{"                    Statusbar                       " link GR_main_bottom} |
 +------------------------------------------------------+

This part of the main page displays the data for all years you defined. Any year in the current project is displayed as a single entry in the list, together with a sum over all costs this year and a sum over all fixed costs of this year. The column "Status" is not yet in use.

The @{b}"Add"@{ub} button will add a new year to the list by incrementing the last year by one. You can change the value for the starting year at the @{"preferences window" link "WI_prefs"}. All fix costs previously defined will automatically be applied to the new year.

The @{b}"Remove"@{ub} button removes the marked year from the list.

The @{b}"Fix costs"@{ub} button will open the @{"fix cost window" link WI_fixcost_definer} which lets you add, remove and modify existing fix costs which start in the currently selected year.

@{"Show a GIF image of this window" link "pics/main_1.gif/main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_reg_months "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / A.2 Months Page"

@{b}A.2 Months Register Page@{ub} - (Part of main window)

 +---------------------------------------------------------+
 | @{"        Toolbar        " link GR_tb_main}                                 |
 |                                                         |
 |  |@{"Years" link GR_reg_years}|            |@{bg shine}@{fg fill}Months@{fg text}@{bg background}|                            |
 |  |------|------------+@{bg shine}      @{bg background}+---------------+ @{bg shine}   1997  @{bg background} |
 |  |@{bg shine}@{fg fill}Month  Sum    Fix   Private Business Other@{fg text}@{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}Janua  466.33 90.21 329.54  24.23    12.56@{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                          @{bg background}|           |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 |  |@{bg shine}                                          @{bg background}|           |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                          @{bg background}| @{"  Edit   " link WI_month_edit} |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                          @{bg background}|   Sum:    |
 |  |@{bg shine}                                          @{bg background}| @{bg shine}   983.23@{bg background} |
 |  +------------------------------------------+           |
 | @{"                      Statusbar                        " link GR_main_bottom} |
 +---------------------------------------------------------+

The register page labeled "Months" displays the months of the year selected at the @{"Years-page" link GR_reg_years}. The list contains all months with some data about the costs that occur in them.

The columns have the following meaning:

  month    -  indicates the month
  sum      -  is the complete sum of costs in this month including fixed costs.
  fix      -  is the sum over all fix costs in this month.
  private  -  is the sum over all costs in the "Private" section.
  business -  is the sum over all costs in the "Business" section.
  others   -  is the sum over all costs in the "Others" and the user defined
              sections.

The text field at the upper right corner of the page displays the year which has been selected at the "Years" register.

The @{b}"Edit"@{ub} button opens the @{"month editor window" link WI_month_edit} which lets you add, remove and edit cost entries for the selected month in the list. You may also open the editor by double clicking at the desired entry.

The "Sum" field at the right bottom displays the sum over all costs, this year.

@{"Show a GIF image of this window" link "pics/main_2.gif/main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_tb_main "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / A.3 Toolbar"

@{b}A.3 The Toolbar@{ub}

The toolbar let's you access the different parts of Money97 more easily. The buttons have the following functions (from left to right):

 * @{b}Clear@{ub} - Clears all entries and starts a new project. (1)
 * @{b}Open@{ub}  - Opens an already existing project. (1)
 * @{b}Save@{ub}  - Saves the actual project. (2)
 * @{b}Print@{ub} - Prints the marked entries. (3)
 * @{b}Prefs@{ub} - Opens the @{"Preferences Window" link WI_prefs}. (2)
 * @{b}Stats@{ub} - Shows you a simple bar chart of the selected entries. (3)

(1) Of course Money97 will warn you if you select this without saving your actual project first.

(2) You can only save projects and load or save the prefs if you already @{"registered" link register} Money97.

(3) These functions will be included in future versions.

Like most buttons in Money97 the toolbar buttons use bubble help, so you can always see what they will do by placing your mouse pointer over them and wait until the bubble is displayed.

---

If you don't like the images of the toolbar you can create your own images. Just take a standard drawing application for the Amiga to do so. The images should be of same size, but need not. You need a new, open, save, print, preferences and a barchart button. These images must then be placed into the drawer "Money97/images/" and named "def_xxxx" as the already installed ones. Please have a look at the filenames. Currently button sets for MagicWB and with 8 and 16 colors are included in the Money97 distribution.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_main_bottom "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / A.4 Status"

@{b}A.4 The Status-Display@{ub}

The status display at the bottom of the main window informs you about the current project. It shows...

 - the project's name
 - the number of years in the project
 - the total number of cost entries
 - the sum of all costs over all years in the project
@ENDNODE

   --------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE WI_fixcost_definer "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B. The Fixcost Definer"

@{b}B.The Fixcost Definer@{ub}

 +----------------------------------------------------------+
 | @{"               Starting with year: 1997                 " link TX_fc_intervall} |
 | @{"                   Fixcosts so far:                     " link GR_fc_subgrp_3} |
 | @{bg fill}@{fg shine}Title    Cost Section Start Stop J F M A M J J A S O N D@{fg text}@{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}Rent      740 Private  1997  n/a x x x x x x x x x x x x@{fg text}@{bg background} |
