 |                                                          |
 | -----------------------@{"  Period  " link GR_fc_subgrp_5}----------------------- |
 | @{bg shine}  Every month every year  @{bg background}    @{bg shine}        January           @{bg background} |
 | -------------------------------------------------------- |
 | @{"Jan" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Feb" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Mar" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Apr" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"May" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Jun" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} |
 | @{"Jul" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Aug" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Sep" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Oct" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Nov" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} @{"Dec" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} @{bg shine}0.00@{bg background} |
 | -------------------------------------------------------- |
 | @{"       Add        " link GR_fc_subgrp_4} @{"     Remove      " link GR_fc_subgrp_4} @{"      Update      " link GR_fc_subgrp_4} |
 |                                       @{bg fill}        OK        @{bg background} |
 +----------------------------------------------------------+

This editor manages costs that occur in a repeating manner, such as rents, incomes, assurances etc. These costs will be called "fix costs" in both program and documentation. The upper part of the window is covered by a list of the so far defined fix costs. Fix costs always start in the year which is displayed at the @{"info-line" link TX_fc_intervall} at the top of the window.

All fix costs are displayed in a @{"listview" link GR_fc_subgrp_3}. At the lower part of the window you will find the four groups @{"description" link GR_fc_subgrp_1}, @{"period" link GR_fc_subgrp_5}, @{"months" link GR_fc_subgrp_2} and @{"action knobs" link GR_fc_subgrp_4}.

@{"Show a GIF image of this window" link "pics/fc.gif/main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE TX_fc_intervall   "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B.1 The Information Line"

@{b}B.1 The Information Line@{ub}

The line at the top of the fix costs window tells you what year you refer to, when you define new fix costs. All fix cost entries you add or update will start with this year so make sure, that you selected the correct year at the @{"years register" link GR_reg_years}. To avoid unwanted modification of the start year after changing some other data a safety requester will ask for permission to change the start year before doing so.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_fc_subgrp_3 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B.2 Fixcost Listview"

@{b}B.2 The Fixcost Listview@{ub}

 |                                                          |
 | @{bg fill}                   Fixcosts so far:                     @{bg background} |
 | @{bg fill}@{fg shine}Title    Cost Section Start Stop J F M A M J J A S O N D@{fg text}@{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}Rent      740 Private  1997  n/a x x x x x x x x x x x x@{fg text}@{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}Newspaper 120   Other  1997 1999 x - - - - - x - - - - -@{fg text}@{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}Water     140 Private  1997  n/a x - - x - - x - - x - -@{fg text}@{bg background} |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}Car Assu. 492 Private  1997  n/a - - x - - - - - x - - -@{fg text}@{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}                                                        @{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}                                                        @{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}                                                        @{bg background} |
 | -------------------------------------------------------- |
 |                                                          |

The columns of the listview display "Title", "Costs" and "Section" of a fix cost entry and also the years this fix cost starts and ends. The year a fix cost ends can be defined using the @{"month editor window" link WI_month_edit} by deleting this fix cost. The starting year is set automatically by the selections at the @{"Year register" link GR_reg_years}.

Due to the single lined layout of the list view the cost column can only be displayed if all entered costs have the same value, otherwise this entry will be marked in a different color without showing the costs. The single monthly entries this editor creates can easily be checked at the @{"month editor window" link WI_month_edit}.

In addition the list view contains a small table of all months. All months in which a cost defined by your fix cost entry occurs are marked with a "x", all others with a "-".
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_fc_subgrp_1 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B.3 Description"

@{b}B.3 The Description Group@{ub}

This group contains two gadgets, one for the @{b}title@{ub} of a fix cost entry and one for a @{b}section@{ub} this fix cost belongs to. Near the string gadgets you find a button which gives you a pop up list, from which you may choose an entry by double clicking at it. The list connected to the "Title" entry gadget contains the titles you have already used so far. You can change the number of titles Money97 remembers at the @{"preferences window" link WI_prefs}.

The list connected to the "Section" entry gadget contains a list of sections the user may define and the three default sections "Private", "Business" and "Others" which can not be removed or renamed (yet). You can add more sections at the @{"preferences window" link WI_prefs}. User defined sections will always be added to the sum in the "Others" column of all list views.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_fc_subgrp_5 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B.4 Period Group"

@{b}B.4 The Period Group@{ub}

This group contains two cycle gadgets which together define the period of the new or marked fix cost. The left gadget defines a period, the right defines a start month. The right gadget is only needed for the last two of the "Period" entries you may choose from the left cycle gadget which need to define a starting month. It will be disabled for the other selections.

This may be best understood with an example:

Selecting:
   "Every Month Every Year, Starting with"
at the left gadget will enable the right gadget and setting this to
   "July"
will result in a fix cost which will appear every year during the months
   July, August, September, October, November, December.

Please refer to the @{"Tutorial" link tutorial} for some more examples.

---

You can choose the following periods at the left cycle gadget:

* @{b}This year@{ub}
This is the most simple kind of fix cost. Enter your cost at the string gadget of the month it occurs and add it to the list. Please note, that you can enter several different costs for several months and Money97 will automatically generate several cost entries out of this.

* @{b}Every year@{ub}
Use this type for costs which occur every year, starting with the selected year. If you add a new year to your list, these costs will also be active for this year. As above you can enter different costs for different months and will get several entries out of this.

* @{b}2 times this year@{ub}
Same as "This year", but this time only the first 6 month gadgets will be enabled. Enter your cost at the string gadget of the month it first occurs and Money97 will automatically fill in the same amount 6 months later, e.g. at july if you entered at january. Please note, that this will not be shown at the string gadgets, have a look at the @{"list view" link GR_fc_subgrp_3} instead.

* @{b}2 times every year@{ub}
Same as above, but works for all following years including the selected one.

* @{b}4 times this year@{ub}
Same as "2 times this year", but inserts the cost every 3 months, e.g. at april, july and september if you entered your cost at january.

* @{b}4 times every year@{ub}
Same as above, but works for all following years too.

* @{b}Every month this year@{ub}
Should be selfexplainig. Only the string gadget for january will be enabled, enter your cost here and it will be inserted for all following months automatically.

* @{b}Every month every year@{ub}
Same as above, but works for all following years too.

* @{b}Every month this year, starting with@{ub}
Same as "Every month this year", but in addition you can select the month your cost will start using the cycle gadget to the right. Note, that you still have to enter your cost at the string gadget of january, all the others will be disabled since this period function only accepts a single cost value. You can check in the list view, that everything works right.

* @{b}Every month every year, starting with@{ub}
Same as above, but works for all following years too.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_fc_subgrp_2 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B.5 Months Group"

@{b}B.5 The Months Group@{ub}

This group contains the fields for the costs of the months which belong to the actual fix cost. You have to enter the cost value of the fix cost into one or more of these fields, this depends on the entry you chose from the @{"period cycle" link GR_fc_subgrp_5}. Some fields may also be disabled, according to the selected entry from this cycle.

If you define a fixcost which occurs 2 or 4 times a year, Money97 will only allow to enter a value into the first 6 or 3 gadgets and assumes the costs to appear at equal time intervals. For an example, have a look at the @{"Tutorial" link tutorial} "assurance entry" for the car.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_fc_subgrp_4 " 4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / B.6 Action Knobs"

@{b}B.6 The Action Knobs Group@{ub}

The buttons at the bottom of the fix cost editor will do the following:

* @{b}"Add"@{ub} your actual data as a new entry to the list of defined fix costs.

* @{b}"Remove"@{ub} deletes the selected fix cost entry from the list.

* @{b}"Update"@{ub} the selected entry with the fields' contents.
@ENDNODE

   -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE WI_month_edit  "4.3 Money97 - C. Cost Editor For A Specified Month"

@{b}C.The Cost Editor For A Specified Month@{ub}

 +----------------------------------------------------------+
 | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}     Month: February (1997)     @{fg text}@{bg background}                         |
 | @{"Date    Title      Costs Section" link GR_me_subgrp_2}                         |
 | @{bg shine}11.2.97 New TV   1119.90 Private@{bg background}   @{"Date:" link GR_me_subgrp_5}    @{bg shine}            @{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}19.2.97 Gift       20.00 Babsi  @{bg background}   @{"Title:" link GR_me_subgrp_5}   @{bg shine}            @{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}20.2.97 Shopping   57.92 Private@{bg background}   @{"Section:" link GR_me_subgrp_5} @{bg shine}            @{bg background} |
 | @{bg shine}24.2.97 Cinema     12.00 Private@{bg background}   @{"Costs:" link GR_me_subgrp_5}   @{bg shine}        @{bg background} ($) |
 | @{bg shine}26.2.97 Shopping   62.12 Private@{bg background}   @{"Clear" link GR_me_subgrp_6}@{"Add" link GR_me_subgrp_6}@{"Update" link GR_me_subgrp_6}@{"Remove" link GR_me_subgrp_6}|  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 | @{bg shine}26.2.97 Milkman     7.80 Private@{bg background}                         |
 | @{bg shine}    @{b}n/a Rent      720.00 Private@{ub}@{bg background}                         |
 | @{bg shine}                                @{bg background}                         |
 | @{bg shine}                                @{bg background}                         |
 | @{bg shine}                                @{bg background}                         |
 |                                                          |
 | @{"Sum" link GR_me_subgrp_3}             @{bg shine}-1999.74@{bg background} Fixcost: @{bg shine}-720.00@{bg background}        @{bg fill}  OK  @{bg background}  |
 +----------------------------------------------------------+

This editor is used for costs that occur unregularly or just once, e.g. your last holiday, the Ferrari you bought yesterday, etc.

Same as all other editors of this program this one also consists of a @{"list view" link GR_me_subgrp_2} at the left side of the window. Below this list you see a @{"group" link GR_me_subgrp_3} consisting of one button with a summation symbol and two fields for sums. At the right side of the window you see a group containing @{"entry fields" link GR_me_subgrp_5} which will enable you to enter or modify the data of a cost entry. The @{"buttons below" link GR_me_subgrp_6} are needed to clear, add, update or remove your entry.

@{"Show a GIF image of this window" link "pics/mon.gif/main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_me_subgrp_2 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / C.1 Listview"

@{b}C.1 The List Of Costs For A Month@{ub}

This list contains all costs that occur this month. Bold typed cost entries without a date are fix cost entries. You may not edit fix costs from within the @{"month editor" link WI_month_editor}, but you can "delete" them. Deleting a fixcost will result in stopping this fixcost the year before the selected one.

Consider for example a fix cost which has started in year 1995 and repeats every year. Lets suppose we have opened the month editor for the April 1998. If we now delete the fix cost entry the above fix cost will be valid only from 1995 till 1997. Starting with year 1998 this cost will no longer be applied to following years. Cost values displayed in white are negative values. The leading minus sign has been removed for a better outfit. You may enter negative values for your income or your costs. This way you can easily see how much money is left for a specific month.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_me_subgrp_3 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / C.2 Summation Group"

@{b}C.2 The Summation Group@{ub}

This group contains fields that display the total sum and the sum of fix costs for this month. Entering new costs in this month will NOT automatically update these fields, but you can do this by hitting the knob with the summation symbol on it. These fields will always be updated whenever the editor window is opened.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_me_subgrp_5 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / C.3 Entry fields"

@{b}C.3 The Entry Fields For A Cost@{ub}

The field labled with "Title" will contain the title of the new or edited cost. The field labeled "Section" will show a section which describes the kind of cost a bit more than only the title. The field labeled "Date" defines the date the cost appears. Since year and month are already selected at the register pages of the main window, you only need to specify the day the cost occurs.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_me_subgrp_6 "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / C.4 Action Knobs"

@{b}C.4 The Action Knobs@{ub}

The buttons have the following functions (from left to right):

   @{b}"Clear"@{ub} the contents of the field to allow a new entry.

   @{b}"Add"@{ub} the contents of the fields as a new entry.

   @{b}"Update"@{ub} the marked entry with the fields' contents.

   @{b}"Remove"@{ub} the marked entry from the list.
@ENDNODE

   -------------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE WI_prefs "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / D. Preferences"

@{b}D.The Preferences Window@{ub}

 +---------------------------------------------+
 |                                             |
 |  |@{"General" link GR_prefs_general}|         |@{"Sections" link GR_sparte_col}|              |
 |  |        +---------|--------|-----------+  |
 |  |                                       |  |
 |  |         --- Title Memory ---          |  |
 |  | Max. remember @{bg fill}   @{bg shine}20@{bg fill}                  @{bg background} |  |
 |  | Add is default?@{bg fill} @{bg background} Entry completition?@{bg fill} @{bg background} |  |
 |  |           --- Currency ---            |  |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 |  | Label @{bg shine}DM        @{bg background}  Position @{bg fill}x@{bg shine}  Right  @{bg background} |  |
 |  |        --- Number Format ---          |  |
 |  | Format String: @{bg shine}%3.2f                 @{bg background} |  |
 |  |    --- First year of project ---      |  |
 |  | First year: @{bg shine}1997                     @{bg background} |  |
 |  |                                       |  |
 |  +---------------------------------------+  |
 |                                @{bg fill}     OK     @{bg background} |
 +---------------------------------------------+

The preferences window allows the user to adjust the programs behaviour and set some default values. The window only contains a single register group with two pages. The @{"first page" link GR_prefs_general} contains general data, the @{"second page" link GR_sparte_col} contains a list with sections and some buttons to add, remove and edit new or existing sections.

Please note, that Money97 refuses to load or save any prefs files if you are using an unregistered version of the program. Click here to @{"register" link register}.
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_prefs_general  "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / D.1 First Page"

@{b}D.1 The First Register Page - General Prefs@{ub}

 +---------------------------------------------+
 |                                             |
 |  |@{fg shine}General@{fg text}|          |@{"Sections" link GR_sparte_col}|              |
 |  |        +---------|--------|-----------+  |
 |  |                                       |  |
 |  |         --- Title Memory ---          |  |
 |  | Max. remember @{bg fill}   @{bg shine}20@{bg fill}                  @{bg background} |  |
 |  | Add is default?@{bg fill} @{bg background} Entry completition?@{bg fill} @{bg background} |  |
 |  |           --- Currency ---            |  |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 |  | Label @{bg shine}DM        @{bg background}  Position @{bg fill}x@{bg shine}  Right  @{bg background} |  |
 |  |        --- Number Format ---          |  |
 |  | Format String: @{bg shine}%3.2f                 @{bg background} |  |
 |  |    --- First year of project ---      |  |
 |  | First year: @{bg shine}1997                     @{bg background} |  |
 |  |                                       |  |
 |  +---------------------------------------+  |
 |                                @{bg fill}     OK     @{bg background} |
 +---------------------------------------------+

This register page contains some subgroups with general preferences for Money97. The upper group "Title memory" defines the behaviour of the program when the user enters unknown titles for cost entries. The maximum number of titles the program remembers and shows you in all pop up lists can be changed using the slider. If more titles than defined are entered, the oldest titles will always be removed. The names of all titles used in a project will be saved with the project file.

The "Add is default" checkbox defines the way the program handles new unknown titles. If it is checked, any new unknown title will be added to the list. If it is not, a requester will ask if it should be added to the list or not. Phrase completition is not yet implemented.

The second group "Currency" contains an entry for the currency label and a cycle gadget which defines whether the lable should appear left or right of the number.

The group at the bottom "Number Format" contains an entry for a C-style number format string. Some examples are given in the pop up list, but the use of "%3.2f" is recommended. This will give you all values with two numbers after the point.

At the bottom of this register you can enter the year you wish to start your projects with by default. Remembering that the "Add" button at the main window will always add a new year by increasing this value by one this enables you to create projects including years before 1997.

@{"Show a GIF image of this window" link "pics/pref_1.gif/main"}
@ENDNODE

@NODE GR_sparte_col  "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / D.2 Second Page"

@{b}D.2 The Second Register Page - Section List Prefs@{ub}

 +---------------------------------------------+
 |                                             |
 |  |@{"General" link GR_prefs_general}|         |@{fg shine}Sections@{fg text}|              |
 |  |--------+---------|        +-----------+  |
 |  | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}business@{fg text}                    @{bg background}   @{bg fill} Add  @{bg background} |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}others@{fg text}                      @{bg background}   @{bg fill}Remove@{bg background} |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}@{fg fill}private@{fg text}                     @{bg background}   @{bg fill} Edit @{bg background} |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}car                         @{bg background}   @{bg shine}*New* @{bg background} |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}*New*                       @{bg background}          |  |  @{"Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!" link ASCII}
 |  | @{bg shine}                            @{bg background}          |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}                            @{bg background}          |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}                            @{bg background}          |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}                            @{bg background}          |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}                            @{bg background}          |  |
 |  | @{bg shine}                            @{bg background}          |  |
 |  +---------------------------------------+  |
 |                                @{bg fill}     OK     @{bg background} |
 +---------------------------------------------+

This page defines the section list. Three sections (white) are default sections, which can neither be deleted nor edited. You may easily add, remove or edit own additional sections which will be shown in black. This list of sections will always been shown if you click at the pop up button near a "Section" string gadget. All user defined sections will always added to the costs of the "Others" section in the monthly and yearly list views.

@{"Show a GIF image of this window" link "pics/pref_2.gif/main"}
@ENDNODE

   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE menu "4.3 Money97 - Online Docs / E. Pull Down Menus"

@{b}E.The Pull Down Menus@{ub}

@{b}Project@{ub}

* About
  Shows some info about Money97

* About MUI
  Shows some info about MUI

* User
  Shows some info about the user who registered this copy of Money97

* New
  Clears all data and starts a new project

* Open
  Loads a previously saved project

* Save
  Saves the actual project (1)

* Save Prefs
  Saves the actual preferences (1)

* Print
  Dumps the selected entry to your printer (2)

* Quit
  Exits from Money97

@{b}Edit@{ub}

* Fixed costs
  Opens the @{"fix cost editor" link WI_fixcost_definer}

* Preferences
  Opens the @{"preferences window" link WI_prefs}

---
(1) You have to @{"register" link register} Money97 to use these functions.

(2) This will be included in future versions.

Some of these functions are also reachable by the @{"toolbar" link toolbar}.
@ENDNODE

   ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

@NODE hints  "Money97 - Online Docs / Hints for using Money97"

@{b}4.4 Hints for using Money97@{ub}

Hey, it's a tool, not a game! ;*)
