@NODE ASCII "Money97 - Online Docs / ASCII Graphics"

@{b}Ieeks, ASCII-Grafx?!?!@{ub}

Yes, I know. ASCII graphics don't look very nice, especially if you are using a proportional font and the button images for marking textlinks (which is default for both MultiView and AmigaGuide).

But during development of this document we found, that showing the descripted window with it's groups is much more intuitive to understand than the pure text so we kept them.

If you really dislike those graphics you can do the following:

@{b}1.@{ub} Ignore them and take a look at Money97 itself while you are reading the docs.

@{b}2.@{ub} Ignore them and take a look at the GIF image of the window which can be reached at the end of the section.

@{b}3.@{ub} If you have a good WWW-Browser, use the HTML documentation instead. Here all GIF images are shown directly as <IMAGEMAP>'s, so you can click a button at the image to read about it's meaning.

@{b}4.@{ub} Improve the outfit of the ASCII graphics by making sure, that you selected a non-proportional font in your Prefs/Font for system texts (which makes sense in many other cases too) and changing the outfit of links from buttons to something like a coloured or underlined font using the Env variables of MultiView to make all lines same length.
@ENDNODE

